  "text": "## LibreOffice Calc Formula Evaluation Chain\n\n### Overview\nFormula evaluation in LibreOffice Calc follows a three-stage pipeline: **Compilation** → **Recalculation Scheduling** → **Interpretation & Execution**.\n\n### Stage 1: Formula Compilation (Tokenization)\n\n**Files:**\n- `sc/source/core/tool/compiler.cxx` - Primary Calc compiler\n- `formula/source/core/api/FormulaCompiler.cxx` - Generic formula compiler\n\n**Key Class:** `ScCompiler` in compiler.cxx\n\n**Entry Point:** `ScCompiler::CompileString(const OUString& rFormula)`\n- Parses formula text (e.g., \"=SUM(A1:A10)\")\n- Produces `ScTokenArray` (bytecode representation)\n- Handles operator precedence, function recognition, and cell references\n- Generates reverse Polish notation (RPN) bytecode\n\n**Token Array:** Defined in `include/formula/tokenarray.hxx`\n- Contains sequence of `FormulaToken` objects\n- Each token has an opcode (ocPush, ocAdd, ocSum, etc.)\n- Stores recalculation mode metadata (`ScRecalcMode`)\n\n### Stage 2: Recalculation Scheduling\n\n**Recalculation Modes** (from `include/formula/tokenarray.hxx`):\n```cpp\nenum class ScRecalcMode : sal_uInt8 {\n    NORMAL         = 0x10,  // Normal recalc on dependency change\n    ALWAYS         = 0x01,  // Always recalculate (volatile functions)\n    ONLOAD_MUST    = 0x02,  // Must recalculate after file load\n    ONLOAD_ONCE    = 0x04,  // Recalculate once after load\n    ONLOAD_LENIENT = 0x08,  // Lenient recalc after load\n    FORCED         = 0x20,  // Force recalc even if not visible\n    ONREFMOVE      = 0x40   // Recalc if referenced cell moved\n}\n```\n\n**Key Classes & Methods:**\n\n1. **ScFormulaCell** (`sc/inc/formulacell.hxx` / `sc/source/core/data/formulacell.cxx`)\n   - Represents a single cell containing a formula\n   - Member: `pCode` - pointer to `ScTokenArray`\n   - Member: `bDirty` - flag indicating cell needs recalculation\n   - Member: `aResult` - cached formula result (`ScFormulaResult`)\n   - Member: `mxGroup` - reference to formula group for optimization\n\n2. **SetDirty() & SetDirtyVar()** in formulacell.cxx\n   - Called when cell's dependencies change\n   - Marks cell for recalculation\n   - Broadcasts to dependent cells via `SvtListener` mechanism\n\n3. **CalcFormulaTree()** in document.cxx\n   - Main recalculation engine\n   - Walks formula tree and interprets all dirty cells\n   - Respects recalculation mode flags\n\n### Stage 3: Interpretation & Execution\n\n**Primary Interpreter Files:**\n- `sc/source/core/tool/interpr4.cxx` - Main interpreter with entry point\n- `sc/source/core/tool/interpr1.cxx` through `interpr8.cxx` - Function implementations\n- `sc/source/core/inc/interpre.hxx` - Class definition\n\n**Execution Flow:**\n\n1. **ScFormulaCell::Interpret()**  in formulacell.cxx (line ~1500)\n   - Entry point called during recalculation cycle\n   - Handles formula groups (optimized batch execution)\n   - Manages recursion detection and circular reference handling\n\n2. **ScFormulaCell::InterpretTail()** in formulacell.cxx (line ~1885)\n   - Internal method for single cell interpretation\n   - Creates `ScInterpreterContext` for execution context\n   - Instantiates `ScInterpreter` object\n   - Calls `ScInterpreter::Interpret()`\n\n3. **ScInterpreter::Interpret()** in interpr4.cxx (line ~3976)\n   - Main bytecode interpreter loop\n   - Iterates through `FormulaTokenIterator aCode` (iterates token array)\n   - For each token:\n     - If opcode is `ocPush`: push value onto stack\n     - Otherwise: execute operation (function call, operator, etc.)\n   - Stack-based evaluation (Forth-like)\n   - Handles matrix formulas, jump conditions, error propagation\n\n4. **Operation Handlers** - `ScInterpreter::ScXXX()` methods\n   - **interpr1.cxx**: ScIf, ScChoose, ScSum, ScCount, ScAnd, ScOr, etc.\n   - **interpr2.cxx**: ScGetActDate, ScInt, ScAbs, ScSin, ScCos, etc.\n   - **interpr3.cxx**: ScVLookup, ScHLookup, ScMatch, ScIndex, etc.\n   - **interpr6.cxx**: ScSum, ScCount, ScAverage, ScMin, ScMax, etc.\n   - **interpr7.cxx**: Statistical functions (ScNorm, ScErf, etc.)\n\n5. **Result Storage**\n   - Result pushed onto internal `ScStack` during interpretation\n   - Final result stored in `ScFormulaCell::aResult` (type `ScFormulaResult`)\n   - Result can be double, string, matrix, or error code\n\n### Supporting Components\n\n**ScInterpreterContext** (`sc/source/core/tool/interpretercontext.cxx` / `sc/inc/interpretercontext.hxx`)\n- Manages interpreter execution context\n- Thread-local context pools for parallel evaluation\n- Maintains formatter, document references, and token caches\n- Provides `ScInterpreterContextGetterGuard` for safe context access\n\n### Example: Evaluating =SUM(A1:A10)\n\n1. **Compile Phase**\n   - `ScCompiler::CompileString(\"=SUM(A1:A10)\")`\n   - Produces token array: [ocPush(range A1:A10), ocSum, ocStop]\n\n2. **Dirty Flagging**\n   - Any change to A1:A10 calls `SetDirty()` on dependent cells\n   - Marks cells with `ScRecalcMode::NORMAL` for recalculation\n\n3. **Recalculation**\n   - `CalcFormulaTree()` finds all dirty formula cells\n   - Respects recalculation mode: ONLOAD_MUST cells recalc after load, ALWAYS cells recalc every time\n\n4. **Interpretation**\n   - `ScFormulaCell::Interpret()` called\n   - Creates `ScInterpreter` and calls `Interpret()`\n   - Reads token array:\n     - Push A1:A10 range onto stack\n     - Execute `ocSum` → calls `ScInterpreter::ScSum()`\n     - Sums all numeric values in range\n     - Result pushed onto stack\n   - Result stored in `aResult`\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Token Array Caching**: Compiled bytecode reused across recalculations\n2. **Formula Grouping**: Multiple cells with identical formula patterns batched together\n3. **Lazy Evaluation**: Cells only interpreted when needed (dirty flag)\n4. **Stack-Based**: RPN evaluation model avoids recursion depth issues\n5. **Context Pooling**: Thread-safe interpreter contexts for parallel evaluation\n6. **Circular Reference Detection**: `RecursionHelper` detects and handles cycles\n7. **Volatile Functions**: Functions like NOW, TODAY, RAND marked ALWAYS to recalc every time"
}

